===message:It can be due to a lack of cones, but it also may be due to a gene mutation. THGe RGB pigments are proteins with retinalk attached. THe porteins result from gene expression. Genes mutate and can be passed on as dominant and recessive sex linked genes. Given this, it is not surprising that color vision varies in the population.   
